tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits except for mildly low alkaline phosphatase, which is likely not clinically significant. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of kidney function.
